Bajaj, Coal India, GVK Power, State Bank: India Stocks Preview

-- B y   R u t h   D a v i d   a n d   R a j h k u m a r   K   S h a a w
-- 
2011-05-19T03:29:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-19/bajaj-coal-india-gvk-power-state-bank-india-stocks-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in  India  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the last close.  The Bombay Stock Exchange Sensitive Index, or Sensex, fell
51.15, or 0.3 percent, to 18,086.20. The S&P CNX Nifty Index on
the National Stock Exchange declined 0.3 percent to 5,420.60.
The BSE 200 Index decreased 0.5 percent to 2,240.38. Nifty
futures for May delivery rose 0.1 percent to 5,434 as of 11:29
a.m. in  Singapore .  Reliance ADA Group: Billionaire Anil Ambani’s,  Reliance
Communications Ltd. (RCOM)    Reliance MediaWorks Ltd. (RMW)  
and  Reliance Power Ltd. (RPWR)   may invest as much as $10
billion in Indonesia, Gita Wirjawan, chairman of the Southeast
Asian country’s Investment Coordinating Board, said after a
meeting between Ambani and Indonesian President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono in Jakarta yesterday. Reliance Communications shares
dropped 3.4 percent to 85.95 rupees, Reliance MediaWorks
declined 2.5 percent to 134 rupees and Reliance Power fell 1.7
percent to 110.7 rupees.  Coal India Ltd. (COAL)  : Coal stocks at Indian power
plants have fallen to a “critical” level and new units are
being built without guaranteed supplies of the fuel, consulting
firm Gerson Lehrman Group Inc. said in a note.  Separately, Coal India submitted a proposal to the South
Asian nation’s coal ministry to buy a 15 percent stake in
Peabody Energy Corp.’s Wilkie Creek mine in  Australia , the
Economic Times reported. The deal may be worth more than $120
million, it said. Shares of Coal India, the world’s largest
producer of the fuel, declined 6 percent to 373.7 rupees.  Bajaj Auto Ltd. (BJAUT)  : India’s second-largest
motorcycle maker plans to begin exporting its Duke motorcycle to
Brazil by the end of the year, the Hindu Business Line reported,
citing Managing Director Rajiv Bajaj. The shares sank 1.7
percent to 1,287.4 rupees.  GVK Power & Infrastructure Ltd. (GVKP)  : A builder of
airports and utilities controlled by Indian billionaire GV Krishna Reddy is in talks to borrow as much as $850 million to
fund the purchase of two  Hancock Prospecting Pty  coal mines,
said two people with knowledge of the negotiations. GVK will use
the money to pay Hancock $500 million for equity in the mines,
and another $350 million as compensation for costs incurred by
the Australian company for running them, the people said, asking
not to be identified because the discussions are private. GVK
Power slid 2.6 percent to 22.55 rupees.  HCL Technologies Ltd. (HCLT)  : The software developer was
rated “buy” in new coverage by Debashish Mazumdar, an analyst
at Techno Shares & Stocks Ltd., with a price estimate of 584
rupees per share. The shares added 0.2 percent to 504.1 rupees.  State Bank of India (SBIN)  Ltd: The nation’s biggest
lender was cut to “hold” from “outperform” by Punit Srivastava, an analyst at Daiwa Securities Capital Markets with
a price estimate of 2,490 rupees per share. The shares fell 2.4
percent to 2,355.75 rupees.  To contact the reporter on this story:
